These are the only 3 systems I have been able to test the code with.  If you get
it working with any other system, DICE, Storm c++, please email me with the new
code so that I can add it to the archive.

I think for the assembler versions you will have to get hold of the original
Amiga includes.  Not sure who now has rights to these.  Perhaps Amiga
Technologies will make developer status free to us poor students :-)<-<

My thanks to CHRISTIAN A. WEBER for the use of the freely distributable IFF
Library included within this archive.  It should be installed if you wish to use
the IFF functions within the code but can be left out.  I include the entire
distribution with this archive.

